  <h1>Cybersecurity Newsfeed</h1>
  <h2>📅 06/03/26</h2>

  <h2>🛡️ Vulnerabilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cisco patches 48 firewall vulnerabilities</strong>: Cisco issued an urgent advisory for 48 flaws, including two critical RCE bugs in the web-based management interface. Unauthenticated attackers could bypass security or gain full admin control. Updates are available for affected firewall products. <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/vulnerabilities-threats/cisco-48-firewall-vulnerabilities-2-critical" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>WordPress membership plugin exploited</strong>: A critical flaw in a popular plugin allows unauthenticated attackers to bypass registration and create unauthorized admin accounts. Attackers are actively using this access to install malicious plugins and steal data. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/wordpress-membership-plugin-bug-exploited-to-create-admin-accounts/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Zero-click RCE in FreeScout help desk</strong>: Improper handling of email attachments and webhooks in the open-source FreeScout platform allows remote code execution without any user interaction, posing a severe risk to support teams. <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/zeroclick-freescout-bug-remote/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>CISA KEV update (March 2026)</strong>: CISA added five bugs to its catalog, including a critical VMware Aria Operations RCE (CVE-2026-22719), Cisco Catalyst SD-WAN flaws, and a legacy Apple iOS/iPadOS vulnerability. Federal agencies must patch by March 26. <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2026/03/05/cisa-adds-five-known-exploited-vulnerabilities-catalog" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🎯 Adversaries</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>RedEyes targets telcos with Noodle RAT</strong>: Chinese state-sponsored actors are using the "Noodle RAT" backdoor and modular plugins to compromise telecommunications edge devices globally, facilitating long-term intelligence gathering and communications interception. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/chinese-state-hackers-target-telcos-with-new-malware-toolkit/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Wikipedia hit by self-propagating JS worm</strong>: A XSS vulnerability was exploited to inject a worm that vandalized high-traffic articles. The script spread by using the credentials of users viewing affected pages to modify other entries. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/wikipedia-hit-by-self-propagating-javascript-worm-that-vandalized-pages/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>BoryptGrab stealer abuses GitHub Pages</strong>: Attackers are hosting fake developer tool repositories on GitHub Pages to deliver the BoryptGrab malware, which harvests browser credentials and session cookies from infected systems. <a href="https://www.trendmicro.com/en_us/research/26/c/boryptgrab-stealer-targets-users-via-deceptive-github-pages.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Dust Specter targets Iraqi officials</strong>: A focused espionage campaign is using multi-stage malware and tailored spear-phishing to exfiltrate government documents and monitor encrypted communications of high-ranking Iraqi officials. <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2026/03/dust-specter-targets-iraqi-officials.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>New actor UAT-9244 identified by Cisco Talos</strong>: This technically proficient group uses custom-built loaders and targeted phishing to bypass antivirus and maintain persistence within enterprise environments for lateral movement. <a href="https://blog.talosintelligence.com/uat-9244/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📈 Trends</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bing AI promotes fake "OpenClaw" repo</strong>: Search engine optimization and AI recommendations were manipulated to promote a fraudulent GitHub repo that delivered info-stealing malware to developers seeking open-source tools. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/bing-ai-promoted-fake-openclaw-github-repo-pushing-info-stealing-malware/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>AI malware assembly lines emerge</strong>: Nation-state actors are integrating LLMs into their workflows to automate code generation and vulnerability identification, leading to an "industrialization" of cyber warfare and faster attack iteration. <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/cyberattacks-data-breaches/nation-state-actor-ai-malware-assembly-line" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Malicious AI extensions harvest chat logs</strong>: Security researchers found browser extensions disguised as productivity tools that scrape LLM chat histories, potentially exposing proprietary business data and personal secrets. <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/03/05/malicious-ai-assistant-extensions-harvest-llm-chat-histories/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Google reports record 90 zero-days in 2025</strong>: Google's annual review shows a spike in zero-day exploitation, primarily driven by nation-states and commercial surveillance vendors focusing on mobile and browser vulnerabilities. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/google-says-90-zero-days-were-exploited-in-attacks-last-year/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Fake FileZilla site bundles malware</strong>: A typosquatting domain mimicking the official FileZilla site is distributing installers bundled with password-stealing payloads, targeting IT professionals and developers. <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2026/03/fake-filezilla-website-distributes.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>💥 Breaches & Leaks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>FBI detects internal network intrusion</strong>: The FBI disclosed suspicious activity on its internal networks. While the full extent is classified, reports suggest investigative data may have been the target. Investigation into the entry vector is ongoing. <a href="https://cyberscoop.com/fbi-targeted-with-suspicious-activity-on-its-networks/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📚 Others</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Phobos Ransomware admin pleads guilty</strong>: The operator of the Phobos RaaS model faces up to 20 years in prison for coordinating attacks on hundreds of organizations, including schools and hospitals. <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/188984/security/phobos-ransomware-admin-faces-up-to-20-years-after-guilty-plea.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>LeakBase cybercrime forum seized</strong>: International law enforcement took down LeakBase, a hub for selling stolen credentials and exploit kits. The seizure is expected to lead to investigations into the forum's high-profile users. <a href="https://hackread.com/leakbase-cybercrime-hacker-forum-seized/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Ukrainian gambling/trafficking ring dismantled</strong>: Police took down a criminal group that combined illegal online gambling with human trafficking and debt bondage, exploiting vulnerable Ukrainian women through digital recruitment. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/police-dismantles-online-gambling-ring-exploiting-ukrainian-women/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

